<h2>Current Projects</h2>

What the AP Group is up to....<p>


<ul>
  <li> <h4>Cognitive Robotics
       </h4>

       We're trying to solve traditional "core" AI problems in the
       context of embodied systems.  We're also trying to understand
       how naturally intelligent systems work!<p>

       
       See the <!WA5><a
       href="http://www.ai.mit.edu/projects/cognitive-robotics">Cognitive
       Robotics Home Page</a> for more, including
       <ul>
	 <li> Neo-Modular Systems
	 <li> The Imagination Project
	 <li> Natural Communication with Robots
       </ul><p>


       Also see the <!WA6><a href="http://www.ai.mit.edu/projects/cog">Cog Shop
       Home Page</a> for information on an interrelated project.<p>


  <li> <h4> Human/Systems Integration</h4>
       Computers are great for connecting humans together!<p>

       <ul>
	 <li>  We've built <!WA7><A
	 HREF="http://www.ai.mit.edu/projects/sodabot/">
	 SodaBot</A>: A Software Agent Environment and Construction
	 System.
	 <li> We're using SodaBot in <!WA8><a
	      href="http://www.ai.mit.edu/projects/hci/">The
	      Intelligent Room.</a> 
	 <li> We're also working (with <!WA9><a
	      href="http://theory.lcs.mit.edu/~karger">David
	      Karger</a>) on <!WA10><a 
	      href="http://www.ai.mit.edu/projects/haystack/">Haystack</a>, per 
	      user customization for information retrieval. 
       </ul><p>

      
  <li> <h4>Education
       </h4>
       So much to be done!  <p>
       We're currently <!WA11><a
       href="http://www.ai.mit.edu/projects/cs101">Rethinking
       CS101</a> -- see that project's home page for ideas about a new
       approach to introductory computer programming.<p>

       Lots of our work involves using inexpensive robotics in education:
       <ul>
	 <li> <!WA12><a href="http://www.ai.mit.edu/people/las/rbl/rbl.html">The 1993
	      AAAI Robot Building Laboratory</a>. 
	 <li> <!WA13><a
	      href="http://www.ai.mit.edu/people/las/domsch-abstract.html">
	      <em>The
	      6.270 Organizer's Manual</em></a>       
	 <li> Robotics-based Undergraduate Computer Programming Courses.
       </ul><p>

       We also collaborate with the <!WA14><a
       href="http://web.mit.edu/afs/athena.mit.edu/course/other/edgerton/newhome.html">Edgerton
       Center</a> and the <!WA15><a
       href="http://www-caes.mit.edu">Center for Advanced 
       Educational Services</a> 
       (including the Virtual Campus) at MIT.
</ul>
<hr>

<!WA16><img src="http://www.ai.mit.edu/icons/basic/construction3.gif"> This section still under
construction!<p>

